THIS RIP SEEMS TO BE OUT OF SYNC.

4
00:02:00.790 --> 00:02:03.859
In order to fix it. use mkvmerge:

5
00:02:11.167 --> 00:02:13.970
A) Click 'Add' to load the movie
(or just drag the mkv file into mkvmerge)

6
00:02:14.003 --> 00:02:17.608
B) Highlight the AC3 audio track and click
the 'Format specific options' tab.

7
00:02:26.516 --> 00:02:28.652
C) On 'Delay (in ms)'. enter "200" with no quotation marks.

8
00:02:28.719 --> 00:02:30.687
D) Make sure you have enough HDD roo for the new file
before clicking 'Start muxing'.

9
00:02:30.787 --> 00:02:32.856
In a few minutes you should get a properly synched file.
These subs here are synched accordingly.

10
00:02:32.923 --> 00:02:36.827
If you didn't notice anything wrong with the audio
in the first place and want to just leave it as it is.
please re-synch my subs for them no to show up too late.
Set them to -200 ms with Subtitle Workshop or any other software.

11
00:02:46.336 --> 00:02:48.872
Enjoy your movie. :)

